meanings.definition: To climb higher or faster than someone or something else.
meanings.sent1: She was outclimbing her friends on the jungle gym.
meanings.sent2: The mountain goat was outclimbing the hiker effortlessly.
meanings.sent3: The squirrel was outclimbing the birds to reach the top of the tree.
meanings.sent4: The spider was outclimbing its prey to catch it in its web.
meanings.sent5: The determined climber was outclimbing all obstacles in her path.

meanings.definition: The act of surpassing in climbing ability.
meanings.sent1: His outclimbing of the rock wall impressed everyone at the gym.
meanings.sent2: The competition was fierce, but her outclimbing skills secured her victory.
meanings.sent3: The monkey's outclimbing of the zookeeper's attempts to catch it was quite entertaining.
meanings.sent4: Her outclimbing of her fear of heights was a remarkable achievement.
meanings.sent5: The outclimbing of the mountain by the experienced climber was a sight to behold.
